      • isTautology

        public boolean isTautology()
        Check whether the current rule is a tautology.
        Returns:
        true if the current rule is a tautology, i.e., has an unsatisfiable body or a tautological head.

      • isFalsity

        public boolean isFalsity()
        Checks whether the current rule is a falsity.
        Returns:
        true if the current rule represents a falsity, i.e., has a tautological (or non-existent) body and an unsatisfiable (or no-existent) head.
